'''''Owner's Manual''''' is an American [[reality television]] series that airs on [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] and premiered on August 15, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|title=AMC Upfront: 'Breaking Bad' Talk Show, 'Talking Dead' Renewal|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/amc-upfront-breaking-bad-talk-441446|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=17 August 2013|date=April 15, 2013}}</ref> Announced in November 2012, the series' first season consists of eight, half-hour episodes.<ref>{{cite web|last=Willmore|first=Alison|title=Another New Unscripted Series for AMC: The Network Greenlights 'Owner's Manual'|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/television/amc-greenlights-unscripted-series-owners-manual|work=Indie Wire|accessdate=17 August 2013|date=November 28, 2012}}</ref> ''Owner's Manual'' tests whether it is best to read the included ownerâ€™s manual or not by representing each side of the divide in a weekly challenge. [[Ed Sanders (television carpenter)|Ed Sanders]] and Marcus Hunt attempt to operate machinery and technology each week with one man working strictly from the manual and the other using his instincts.<ref>{{cite press release|last=Bibel|first=Sara|title=AMC Greenlights New Unscripted Series 'Owners Manual'|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/11/28/amc-greenlights-new-unscripted-series-owners-manual/159378/|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=17 August 2013|date=November 28, 2012}}</ref>

