==Reception==
Robert Lloyd of The Los Angeles Times says the show is guided by charm and pretense.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/showtracker/la-et-st-owners-manual-review-20130815,0,2689119.story | title=Review: AMC reality show 'Owner's Manual' guided by charm, pretense | work=The Los Angeles Times | accessdate=August 15, 2013}}</ref> Melissa Camacho of Common Sense Media gave the show 3 out of 5 stars saying that while the show is not the most sophisticated of shows, watching how the two handle things is interesting.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/owners-manual | title=Owner's Manual | publisher=Common Sense Media | accessdate=August 15, 2013}}</ref>

